{"descriptions":[{"id":1423,"title":"Sekhang Tekchen Mindröl Gyatso Ling Introduction","content":"\u003cdiv class=\"essay-body\"\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"essay-head2\"\u003e\u003ctable\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"chapter\"\u003e\u003cem\u003eA Survey of Bonpo Monasteries\u003c/em\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"author\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003eby \u003c/span\u003eDondrup Lhagyal, \n\t\tPhuntso Tsering Sharyul, \n\t\tTsering Thar, \n\t\tCharles Ramble and Marietta Kind\u003c!--(l)--\u003e\u003cbr/\u003eEdited by Samten G. Karmay and Yasuhiko Nagano \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"width: 100%; text-align: right;\" align=\"right\" valign=\"top\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"copyright\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\"eng\"\u003e Copyright \u0026copy; 2003. \u003c/span\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"eng\" id=\"permission\"\u003eReproduced with permission from the authors \u003cbr xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\"/\u003eunder the \u003ca href=\"/tools/licenses.php#essay=/thl/text-license/\" class=\"thl-poplink\"\u003eTHL Digital Text License\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"b6-3\"\u003eReb gong \u003c/h2\u003e\n\n                  \u003ch3 id=\"b6-3-6\"\u003e(105) gDong mgo Temple\u003c/h3\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-1\"\u003e1. Name \u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003egSas khang Theg chen smin grol rgya mtsho gling\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-2\"\u003e2. Location \u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003egDong mgo village of sPyi tshang (latitude: 35\u0026deg;32\u0026rsquo;17\u0026rdquo;N, longitude:\n                        102\u0026deg;04\u0026rsquo;00\u0026rdquo;E).\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-3\"\u003e5. Number of practitioners\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eThere are twenty two Bonpo tantric practitioners in the temple.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-4\"\u003e8 / 9. Rituals \u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eKun bzang and \u0026rsquo;Bum pa from the 21st to the 26thday of the 1st month. Kun\n                        bzang on the 10th day of each month. Kun bzang and \u0026rsquo;Bum pa for five days at\n                        a suitable time in the 5th month. sTag la from the 16th to the 21st day of\n                        the 11th month.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-5\"\u003e12. Local community\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003egDong mgo village comprising forty-four families (three hundred and ten\n                        people altogether) is considered as the lha sde of the temple.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-6\"\u003e13. Local festivals\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eThe two \u003cspan xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\" style=\"font-style: italic;\" class=\"\"\u003ela btsas\u003c/span\u003e of mThar smug and Tshe lung are\n                        propitiated on the same day by the people of gDong mgo, rGyal mtsho dpal and\n                        Gad pa skya bo villages.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n                  \n\n                     \u003ch4 id=\"b6-3-6-7\"\u003e14. Economic occupation of the local people\u003c/h4\u003e\n\n                     \u003cp\u003eAgriculture\u003c/p\u003e\n\n                  \n\n               \u003ctable xmlns:str=\"http://exslt.org/strings\" cellspacing=\"8\" align=\"center\" class=\"navarrows\"\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd class=\"leftcell\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"backarrow\" title=\"Previous Section\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-left.gif\" title=\"Previous Section\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd class=\"midcell\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"uparrow\" title=\"Beginning of Article\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-up.gif\" title=\"Beginning of Article\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd class=\"rightcell\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"forwardarrow\" title=\"Next Section\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"/global/images/arrow-right.gif\" title=\"Next Section\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv id=\"chap-id\"\u003e/bonpo-monasteries/b6-3-6/\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"overflow: hidden; height: 300px;\" class=\"jqmWindow\" id=\"chapRefWindow\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"closebtn\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"#\"\u003eClose\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"height: 280px;\" class=\"conx-content\"\u003e\u003ch3\u003eNote Citation for Page \u003cspan class=\"pgnm\"/\u003e\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp class=\"biblref\"\u003eDondrup Lhagyal, Phuntso Tsering Sharyul, Tsering Thar, Charles Ramble, and \n\t\tMarietta Kind, A Survey of Bonpo Monasteries and Temples in\n               Tibet and the Himalaya\n\t\t\t\t(ISBN: ,\t\n\t\t\t\t:, \n\t\t\t\t2010-07-06), \n\t\t\t\t\u003cspan class=\"pgnm\"/\u003e.\n\t\t\t\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch3\u003eBibliographic Citation\u003c/h3\u003e\u003cp\u003eDondrup Lhagyal, Phuntso Tsering Sharyul, Tsering Thar, Charles Ramble, and \n\t\tMarietta Kind. A Survey of Bonpo Monasteries and Temples in\n               Tibet and the Himalaya, . \n\t\t\t\t(ISBN:\\)\t:, 2010-07-06.\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e","source_url":"/places/monasteries/publications/bon-book.php#!book=/bonpo-monasteries/wb/b6-3-6","is_primary":false,"created_at":"2011-12-13 02:29:38 UTC","updated_at":"2011-12-13 02:29:38 UTC","authors":[{"id":"80","fullname":"ཚེ་རིང་ཐར། (Tsering Thar)"},{"id":"80","fullname":"ཚེ་རིང་ཐར། (Tsering Thar)"}]}]}